{"title":"Where Paris-Roubaix will be decided, part 4: Roubaix Velodrome","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/paris-roubaix-velodrome","date":1744372059000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/paris-roubaix-velodrome\">Where Paris-Roubaix will be decided, part 4: Roubaix Velodrome</a></p>\n\n<p>The Champs-Elysées, Alpe d’Huez, Mont Ventoux… all iconic places, although largely for their associations with the Tour de France. There are few races outside of the Tour that can compete, but the venue that hosts the finale of <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/paris-roubaix-all-you-need-to-know\">Paris-Roubaix</a> – the men’s race first run in 1896, making it seven years older than the Tour – certainly comes close.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Roubaix’s velodrome is also known as the Vélodrome André Pétrieux and apparently got its name from a local Roubaix father and son, who shared the same name and were ambassadors for sport in the area. Outside of that one special weekend in April, it is a somewhat desolate-looking place: the empty grandstands, the faded painted lines, the old shower block.</p>\n\n\n\n\n<div>\n<figure><img width=\"647\" height=\"970\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2018/03/02163658/insight_paris_roubaix_09-647x970.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2018/03/02163658/insight_paris_roubaix_09-647x970.jpg 647w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2018/03/02163658/insight_paris_roubaix_09-200x300.jpg 200w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2018/03/02163658/insight_paris_roubaix_09-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2018/03/02163658/insight_paris_roubaix_09-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2018/03/02163658/insight_paris_roubaix_09-750x1125.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2018/03/02163658/insight_paris_roubaix_09-1140x1710.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2018/03/02163658/insight_paris_roubaix_09.jpg 1200w\" /><figcaption>Kevin Faingnaert</figcaption></figure></div>\n\n\n<p>But once the tell-tale chop-chop-chop of the approaching helicopter blades signifies the imminent arrival of the leading riders, the packed-out velodrome suddenly rumbles and bubbles into life. All at once, the images everyone has been watching on the velodrome’s big TV screen is now something visible with their own eyes: cyclists riding straight onto the hallowed track surface.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The track has hosted the denouement of every men’s Paris-Roubaix since 1943, save for the three editions between 1986 and 1988 when it was being resurfaced, and has been the setting of the Paris-Roubaix Femmes finale since its inaugural edition in 2021. Of course, while the pavé sectors are the stars (literally, ranked) of the Roubaix show, the velodrome has the honour of always being the site of the victory.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/subscriptions?utm_source=Web&amp;utm_medium=Banner&amp;utm_campaign=Banner+8\"><img width=\"970\" height=\"300\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/Subs-flash-162-for-web-8-970x300.webp\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/Subs-flash-162-for-web-8-970x300.webp 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/Subs-flash-162-for-web-8-300x93.webp 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/Subs-flash-162-for-web-8-768x238.webp 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/Subs-flash-162-for-web-8-1536x476.webp 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/Subs-flash-162-for-web-8-2048x634.webp 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/Subs-flash-162-for-web-8-750x232.webp 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2025/03/Subs-flash-162-for-web-8-1140x353.webp 1140w\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Agony or ecstasy</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2018/03/07102728/insight_paris_roubaix_08-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"insight_paris_roubaix_08\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2018/03/07102728/insight_paris_roubaix_08-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2018/03/07102728/insight_paris_roubaix_08-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2018/03/07102728/insight_paris_roubaix_08-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2018/03/07102728/insight_paris_roubaix_08-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2018/03/07102728/insight_paris_roubaix_08-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2018/03/07102728/insight_paris_roubaix_08-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2018/03/07102728/insight_paris_roubaix_08-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2018/03/07102728/insight_paris_roubaix_08.jpg 1200w\" /><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Whether solo or fought out between small groups, the finish protocol is always the same after the leaders emerge onto the track: one-and-a-half laps of euphoric or agonising track racing after 260km on the very worst roads northern France can muster. The closest finish came in 1990 when Canada’s Steve Bauer and Belgian Eddy Planckaert were eventually separated by a single centimetre in Planckaert’s favour.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>‘The velodrome is a really special place for me, because the first time I finished there was the time I finished second in 1994,’ says UAE Team Emirates sports director Fabio Baldato, who used to race for Italian team MG Maglificio.</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/mathieu-van-der-poel-paris-roubaix-2024\">The edge of glory: Does history predict a win for Mathieu van der Poel at Paris-Roubaix 2024?</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/how-to-watch-and-live-stream-paris-roubaix\">How to watch Paris-Roubaix 2025</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/paris-roubaix-mons-en-pevele\">Where Paris-Roubaix will be decided, part 2: Mons-en-Pévèle</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/paris-roubaix-carrefour-de-l-arbre\">Where Paris-Roubaix will be decided, part 3: Carrefour de l’Arbre</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/paris-roubaix-arenberg-forest\">Where Paris-Roubaix will be decided, part 1: The Arenberg Forest</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/paris-roubaix-all-you-need-to-know\">Paris-Roubaix 2025 preview: Routes, favourites, how to watch, start lists and history</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<p>‘That was amazing – unbelievable – because there had been mud and cold and snow for the first 100km, and then rain. It was a really epic race. I finished Roubaix more than 10 times, but my favourite memory is when in 2008, aged nearly 40, I finished tenth.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>‘I was thrilled to still be there at the end with the best riders. After I had a bad crash in <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/paris-roubaix-arenberg-forest\">the Arenberg Forest</a> in 1998, there was a period when I hated the race and didn’t want to do it. It took another three or four years before I got my confidence back, which did return, and finishing Roubaix at the velodrome has given me some wonderful memories.’</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/newsletters\"><img width=\"970\" height=\"351\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-2-970x351.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-2-970x351.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-2-300x109.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-2-768x278.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-2-1536x556.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-2-2048x741.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-2-750x271.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2024/10/Newsletter-flash-2-1140x412.jpg 1140w\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/paris-roubaix-velodrome\">Where Paris-Roubaix will be decided, part 4: Roubaix Velodrome</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a>.</p>","author":"Martin James","siteTitle":"Cyclist.co.uk","siteHash":"561486e7070fa5351de9318ad0fa26c2a39332acba5fc7c7d1694a01d53d431e","entryHash":"52d04c202adbd6f682d8f02f9e73b14503481bba51f9a229a602ab7e8663724c","category":"Cycling"}